raw_meta_yaml:
schema_version: 1

context:
  name: igwn-segments
  version: 2.1.1

package:
  name: ${{ name|lower }}
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/i/igwn-segments/igwn_segments-${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 672814d78f5de7582b5f39189cdc6016d7ffde95d2b8b8b8b82aa9b45e53f3dd

build:
  number: 0
  script: ${{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv --no-deps --no-build-isolation
  skip:
    - "python_impl != 'cpython'"

requirements:
  build:
    - ${{ compiler('c') }}
    - ${{ stdlib('c') }}
    # extras for cross-compiling:
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then:
        - cross-python_${{ target_platform }}
        - python
  host:
    - pip
    - python
    - setuptools >=70.0.0
    - setuptools-scm >=8
  run:
    - python

tests:
  - files:
      source:
        - test/
    requirements:
      run:
        - pip
        - pytest >=3.9.1
        - if: not win and not match(python, ">=3.14")
          then: python-lal
    script:
      - python -m pip check
      - python -m pip show igwn-segments
      - python -m pytest test

about:
  summary: Representations of semi-open intervals
  description: |
    This module defines the segment and segmentlist objects, as well as the
    infinity object used to define semi-infinite and infinite segments.
  homepage: https://git.ligo.org/computing/software/igwn-segments/
  repository: https://git.ligo.org/computing/software/igwn-segments.git
  documentation: https://igwn-segments.readthedocs.io/
  license: GPL-3.0-or-later
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - duncanmmacleod
    - lpsinger
    - titodalcanton
